  "description": "Cool-season perennial (cultivated as annual, 70–120 days to harvest). Produces underground stem tubers (swollen stolons) via vegetative propagation from seed-tubers. Purple and blue-fleshed cultivars (Purple Majesty, Purple Viking) accumulate high anthocyanins. Prefers cool soils (15–20°C); poor performance in heat. Direct-plant seed-tubers in spring; hill soil around emerging plants to prevent sunlight-exposed tubers. Moderate water and fertility needs. Cool-season crop distinct from warm-season Solanaceae.",
  "name": "Potato",
